<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[192,1441,1831,1927]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,1831,1857]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Cephalic region wide (cephalic index range 64–89), carapace narrowed (carapace index &lt;60), without thoracic groove but with slight depression instead; PER wider than AER and almost straight to moderately recurved, AME larger than ALE, PME–PME greater than PME–PLE, PLE situated close to lateral margin of
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041777" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5041777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041777/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" startId="4.[192,268,857,883]" targetBox="[195,1440,216,826]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1440,857,952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,296,857,883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Figure 1.</emphasis>
Ecoregion distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Perger &amp; Rubio, 2021" authorityName="Perger &amp; Rubio" authorityYear="2021" box="[591,929,857,883]" class="Arachnida" family="Corinnidae" genus="Myrmecotypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrofemoratus" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[591,929,857,883]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Myrmecotypus rubrofemoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[935,1071,857,884]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[935,1071,857,884]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, according to the regionalization by 
<bibRefCitation author="Navarro G &amp; Ferreira W." box="[227,548,891,918]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="250000" refId="ref4428" refString="Navarro G, Ferreira W. 2011. Mapa de Sistemas Ecologicos de Bolivia, escala 1: 250000. RUMBOL SRL-The Nature Conservancy (TNC); Bolivia. [Edicion CD ROM]" type="journal article" year="2011">Navarro and Ferreira (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. Collection location indicated by red circle, map produced with QGIS (version 2.14.3, http:// www.qgis.org/en/site).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1440,1004,1065]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
cephalic area; abdomen only very slightly petiolated; tibia I ventral spines paired in 2–2, 3–2, 3–3 or 4–4 arrangement; trochanter IV notch usually absent, with only a tiny one, if present (
<bibRefCitation author="Perger R &amp; Rubio GD" box="[1015,1289,1038,1064]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="151 - 164" refId="ref4548" refString="Perger R, Rubio GD. 2020 a. Contributions to the knowledge of Neotropical ant-like spiders: Myrmecotypus tahyinandu sp. n. from Bolivian Chiquitano forest, a new country record for M. niger, and indirect evidence for species-specific mimicry (Araneae: Corinnidae: Castianeirinae). Zootaxa 4790: 151 - 164." type="journal article" year="2020">Perger and Rubio 2020a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
